        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1542695335" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6422413793613992286">For a few semesters, art history was my minor in university. I did not know a lot about art, but I was interested and it seemed fun. If only my courses were as good as this, I would not have given up on this field of study.<br/><br/>Without being condescending or snobby (my main problem with my former teachers and some fellow students), Gombrich writes about art history in a way, that is very exciting and fascinating for the uneducated reader (i.e. me).<br/><br/>The art prints in my edition are extremely beautiful.</span>
  <span id="freeText6422413793613992286" style="display:none">For a few semesters, art history was my minor in university. I did not know a lot about art, but I was interested and it seemed fun. If only my courses were as good as this, I would not have given up on this field of study.<br /><br />Without being condescending or snobby (my main problem with my former teachers and some fellow students), Gombrich writes about art history in a way, that is very exciting and fascinating for the uneducated reader (i.e. me).<br /><br />The art prints in my edition are extremely beautiful.<br /><br />Definitely recommended.</span>
